##Spring Festival observation of an ordinary citizen in Xiangyang, Hubei Province

Material life reference

By Peng Liangjie
Source: Material Life Reference (ID: WZSHCK)

01.

Xiangyang, more than 300 kilometers away from Wuhan, Hubei Province's second largest city in GDP, has long been known as "the place to be fought over by military The Legend of the Condor Heroes" , the place Guo Jing Huang Rong and his wife are sworn to defend in the book the The Legend of the Condor Heroes. Recently, as the persistence of "not closed city" in Hubei city caused concern.

The date of my return to my hometown in Xiangyang, Hubei Province, was January 20, the same day that confirmed cases were reported in many parts of the country and public opinion suddenly turned sour. Before that, I knew very little about the severity of COVID-19 pneumonia.

On the 20th, my partner and I took a Beijing Capital International Airport flight after 10:00 a.m. from Qingdao to Xiangyang. There were no temperature checks at Beijing Capital International Airport Airport, Qingdao airport or Xiangyang Liuji Airport, and only a handful of people wore masks. I was very impressed when I saw a woman in her 30s standing in front of me at the security check at Qingdao airport, with a tight mask and something like plastic wrap wrapped around her hands, presumably to keep the virus at bay. I looked at her a few times.

In the afternoon I in Qingdao airport waiting for more than 5 hours, is the time when public opinion quickly ferments, the news of the epidemic in Wechat Circle of friends, public accounts overwhelming. Around three o'clock, my partner sent me a link to an e-commerce platform to buy a mask and told me to hurry up and buy it. When I clicked on it, it already showed that it was out of stock, just 5 minutes after she placed the order. We went to other stores and found that they were out of stock or could not be sent out until February 4. The price of one store that could deliver the next day doubled. TWENTY-FIVE N95 masks sold for more than 300 yuan. Still, we immediately ordered them to Xiangyang, fearing that they would not be available in the future.

In my impression, SARS hardly affected Xiangyang in 2003. That year I went to junior high school, school is not closed, the memory does not smell of white vinegar, that year's disaster spared our town. After I came to Beijing to attend university, the journalism class will be SARS as a typical case study, I really realize its terrible.

When I first persuaded my family to wear face masks, I did what many young people do: I didn't suffer from SARS, and my elders were stubborn. I was a Veronica Guerin. Go home the next day go out with my mother, at my insistence very reluctantly put on a mask, go out to see, "no one wear, too boring" , a pull down. It turns out that a single word from a parent's friend or peer is more effective than ten words from a child -- unless it's a relative's phone call.

The 21st and 22nd are "vacuum time" , after the public sentiment ferments, has not come from this city's authority data release throughout, the people can only hearsay, "the so-and-so hospital, has a person to check out" . But in the past two days, the number of people wearing masks on the streets has increased by at least half. During the day on the 22nd, the traffic police and the bus driver were well protected.

The connecting flight took place on the afternoon of the 22nd. People's Daily published a report on the situation in Hubei Province. This was followed up: that night, Hubei Province announced the establishment of the COVID-19 pneumonia prevention and control headquarters, holding a news conference; later that night, Xiangyang First reported the number of people infected.

Since the 23rd, my family has been staying at home. It was a cloudy day, standing in front of the window to look out, the Sun will occasionally come out of the clouds for a while, alms a little less solid sunshine. To be honest, I haven't followed the dynamics of a social event this closely in years. Over the past few days, the speed at which information is updated and the density at which it is received have often confused time and made it seem as if the previous day had happened a few hours earlier. The afternoon passed quickly as I sat on the SOFA, brushing up on the latest news and the reports ahead.

Besides waiting, all we can do is take care of ourselves and our families.

Before I left Beijing, I had been worried about going home for the Spring Festival and going on with my work, but now, this has become the least of my worries.

02.

"Shut Down? "

For days on end, every time a message was posted on the official Weibo account of the Xiangyang Daily, the following message focused solely on that one issue.

As a native of Xiangyang, I often tell people of my hometown: Zhuge Liang's former home, Longzhong, is here, and Guo Jing's walled city is here. Now all you have to do is say, "yeah, that's the place that's not sealed. ".

Other cities in Hubei Province followed suit after Wuhan officially closed the city at 2 am on Tuesday, suspending the city's public transport system or closing external railway and coach channels, xiangyang, the second-largest province by GDP, has been slow to make a move. In the eyes of the citizens, the closure of the city is a foregone conclusion, nothing more than a matter of time, just sit back and wait for the boots. The closure of the city in the hearts of people, but to provide a "sense of security. ".

On the 24th, on the 30th day of the Lunar New Year, it was cloudy and rainy. The big family dinner on New Year's Eve has been cancelled.

The rumor of "closing the city" began to ferment that night. Shortly after 6 pm, two friends sent me a series of wechat messages telling me that the city of Xiangyang would be closed at midnight. One of them said it was a message from a police friend.

In front of me was a TV screen with CCTV New Year's Gala, me tweeting, my friends'circle, my mother exchanging voice and video messages with relatives. The 2020 New Year's Eve gala is probably the most watched show in recent years, with many people trapped at home and bored only to revive the tradition, but it may also be the least watched, with so much at stake, after all, the gala can only be heard in the background. Looking back on the Spring Festival gala, I can only remember Xiao Zhan's handsome face.

And before you know it, it's midnight, and there's still no news. In a message posted near midnight to celebrate the New Year, hundreds of people left messages wanting only to know:

Are we going to the end of the line? Can we get a confirmation?

Someone in the message angrily scold, more than angry mood is anxiety.

This year's Spring Festival gala ended earlier than usual. I decided to wait a little longer, considering that the notice to shut down the city in Wuhan had been issued at 2:00 a.m. , but I persisted until 3:00 a.m. The sound of rain dripping outside the window makes one tense in the heart. I'm too tired to wait.

The next morning, Guan Wei refuted rumors, there is no Fengcheng one said. Some call for at least shutting down city buses and stopping some parents whose children are unable to dissuade them from visiting.

My family has been indoors for four days straight. We had plenty of meat for the New Year guests for a few months, but the vegetables had a short shelf life. I asked my mother how long the vegetables would last, and she said two weeks. If we shut down the city, we need to be prepared.

All sorts of "gossip" are flying around, offering short-lived hopes and self-proclaimed prophets.

It wasn't until the evening of the 25th that the Xiangyang Airport was shut down. From the 26th, all seven civil airports in Hubei Province, including the Xiangyang Liuji Airport, will be closed except for the Shenlongjia airport.

Around the same time, traffic was suspended in Florida, but only by long distance buses and buses, and the city's traffic continued to flow as people posted messages on twitter urging the suspension. The latest news is "half run" , the official reason, to maintain "health and safety" under the premise of "basic operation.

03.

So far, "Hubei is not only Wuhan" related topics have gradually received attention. Media reports focused on Huanggang, the province's second most populous city, and the largest of the province's 12 prefecture-level cities after Wuhan, with 122 confirmed cases.

Geographically, Xiangyang lies to the northwest of Hubei, more than 300 kilometers southeast of Hubei, separated by Jingmen and Xiaogan. Under normal circumstances, more than 60 trains depart from the three railway stations in Xiangyang every day, with the shortest journey time being 1 hour 13 minutes (G6818) and the longest 5 hours 13 minutes (K352) .

According to Baidu's migration data, Xiangyang moved up from seventh to fourth place in the ranking of the number of people flowing from Wuhan to surrounding cities from Jan. 16 to Jan. 22, huxiao reported earlier.

But some Xiangyang citizens have begun to describe themselves as "streakers" .

The wechat group in our community sent a return from Wuhan Registration Form, Wechat Group informed you: If there are people back from Wuhan, please register at the gate guard, other than that, no one to ask; On the 22nd, I was going to buy something at a large supermarket. There was a long line at the checkout counter, but few people wore face masks. That stopped me from shopping. It wasn't until the 24th that a text message was sent to my mother's mobile phone reminding residents to go out less, from the Hubei provincial pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters, this is the only one.

Residents in Xiangyang's counties and townships are eager to take neighboring Henan Province as an example of "good management" : Don't you copy homework?

A lot of people are feeling a bit off: Just 25 days ago, official infection notification figures showed that there were no confirmed cases in Xiangyang, and all 49 were suspected of being in Florida -- Xiangyang was not only the last city to close, it is also one of the few cities not yet to have its first confirmed case, as Xiangyang is not named in the daily notification of the disease.

"Is there no reagent box or other reason? Why other cities can be diagnosed but Xiangyang is not the second largest city? " It's another great question on Weibo, except for the lock-up of the city, as if there was no diagnosis, than the number of confirmed cases.

A friend of the third-class Hospital in the city center told me that the hospital did not have the right to test and had to report the samples to the city's epidemic prevention center, so the hospital does not know the exact number of confirmed cases in the hospital, we have to wait for unified notification. Her own assessment is that "this hospital is suspected to be basically a confirmed diagnosis. ".

The latest development is that the data released on the 25th, the first confirmed case in Xiangyang, the latest data on the 26th, eight confirmed, suspected cases of a cumulative 110.

On the 26th, officials finally officially responded to the Query: According to the requirements of relevant state documents, the city and state first confirmed case must be verified by provincial centers for Disease Control and prevention before it can be confirmed as a confirmed case. It takes about 2-3 days for the recheck results to return, which is why the information of confirmed cases was not released until three days after the suspected cases were announced.

From the second case, no longer need provincial CDC audit confirmation, the city can test and confirm the results.

"The number of confirmed cases is increasing rapidly, but it is impossible to tell whether this is due to the disposal of previously untested samples or the fact of new cases, " I read in an article in China Newsweek, john  Johan, a scientist at Johns Hopkins University in the US.

Tomorrow, how many people will be diagnosed?

On the 24th, on the 30th day of the Lunar New Year, it was cloudy and rainy. The big family dinner on New Year's Eve has been cancelled.

The rumor of "closing the city" began to ferment that night. Shortly after 6 pm, two friends sent me a series of wechat messages telling me that the city of Xiangyang would be closed at midnight. One of them said it was a message from a police friend.

In front of me was a TV screen with CCTV New Year's Gala, me tweeting, my friends'circle, my mother exchanging voice and video messages with relatives. The 2020 New Year's Eve gala is probably the most watched show in recent years, with many people trapped at home and bored only to revive the tradition, but it may also be the least watched, with so much at stake, after all, the gala can only be heard in the background. Looking back on the Spring Festival gala, I can only remember Xiao Zhan's handsome face.

And before you know it, it's midnight, and there's still no news. In a message posted near midnight to celebrate the New Year, hundreds of people left messages wanting only to know:

Are we going to the end of the line? Can we get a confirmation?

Someone in the message angrily scold, more than angry mood is anxiety.

This year's Spring Festival gala ended earlier than usual. I decided to wait a little longer, considering that the notice to shut down the city in Wuhan had been issued at 2:00 a.m. , but I persisted until 3:00 a.m. The sound of rain dripping outside the window makes one tense in the heart. I'm too tired to wait.

The next morning, Guan Wei refuted rumors, there is no Fengcheng one said. Some call for at least shutting down city buses and stopping some parents whose children are unable to dissuade them from visiting.

My family has been indoors for four days straight. We had plenty of meat for the New Year guests for a few months, but the vegetables had a short shelf life. I asked my mother how long the vegetables would last, and she said two weeks. If we shut down the city, we need to be prepared.

All sorts of "gossip" are flying around, offering short-lived hopes and self-proclaimed prophets.

It wasn't until the evening of the 25th that the Xiangyang Airport was shut down. From the 26th, all seven civil airports in Hubei Province, including the Xiangyang Liuji Airport, will be closed except for the Shenlongjia airport.

Around the same time, traffic was suspended in Florida, but only by long distance buses and buses, and the city's traffic continued to flow as people posted messages on twitter urging the suspension. The latest news is "half run" , the official reason, to maintain "health and safety" under the premise of "basic operation.

"Shut Down? "

For days on end, every time a message was posted on the official Weibo account of the Xiangyang Daily, the following message focused solely on that one issue.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As a native of Xiangyang, I often tell people of my hometown: Zhuge Liang's former home, Longzhong, is here, and Guo Jing's walled city is here. Now all you have to do is say, "yeah, that's the place that's not sealed. ".

Other cities in Hubei Province followed suit after Wuhan officially closed the city at 2 am on Tuesday, suspending the city's public transport system or closing external railway and coach channels, xiangyang, the second-largest province by GDP, has been slow to make a move. In the eyes of the citizens, the closure of the city is a foregone conclusion, nothing more than a matter of time, just sit back and wait for the boots. 03.

So far, "Hubei is not only Wuhan" related topics have gradually received attention. Media reports focused on Huanggang, the province's second most populous city, and the largest of the province's 12 prefecture-level cities after Wuhan, with 122 confirmed cases.

Geographically, Xiangyang lies to the northwest of Hubei, more than 300 kilometers southeast of Hubei, separated by Jingmen and Xiaogan. Under normal circumstances, more than 60 trains depart from the three railway stations in Xiangyang every day, with the shortest journey time being 1 hour 13 minutes (G6818) and the longest 5 hours 13 minutes (K352) .

According to Baidu's migration data, Xiangyang moved up from seventh to fourth place in the ranking of the number of people flowing from Wuhan to surrounding cities from Jan. 16 to Jan. 22, huxiao reported earlier.

But some Xiangyang citizens have begun to describe themselves as "streakers" .

The wechat group in our community sent a return from Wuhan Registration Form, Wechat Group informed you: If there are people back from Wuhan, please register at the gate guard, other than that, no one to ask; On the 22nd, I was going to buy something at a large supermarket. There was a long line at the checkout counter, but few people wore face masks. That stopped me from shopping. It wasn't until the 24th that a text message was sent to my mother's mobile phone reminding residents to go out less, from the Hubei provincial pneumonia control and Prevention Headquarters, this is the only one.

Residents in Xiangyang's counties and townships are eager to take neighboring Henan Province as an example of "good management" : Don't you copy homework?

A lot of people are feeling a bit off: Just 25 days ago, official infection notification figures showed that there were no confirmed cases in Xiangyang, and all 49 were suspected of being in Florida -- Xiangyang was not only the last city to close, it is also one of the few cities not yet to have its first confirmed case, as Xiangyang is not named in the daily notification of the disease.

"Is there no reagent box or other reason? Why other cities can be diagnosed but Xiangyang is not the second largest city? " It's another great question on Weibo, except for the lock-up of the city, as if there was no diagnosis, than the number of confirmed cases.

A friend of the third-class Hospital in the city center told me that the hospital did not have the right to test and had to report the samples to the city's epidemic prevention center, so the hospital does not know the exact number of confirmed cases in the hospital, we have to wait for unified notification. Her own assessment is that "this hospital is suspected to be basically a confirmed diagnosis. ".

The latest development is that the data released on the 25th, the first confirmed case in Xiangyang, the latest data on the 26th, eight confirmed, suspected cases of a cumulative 110.

On the 26th, officials finally officially responded to the Query: According to the requirements of relevant state documents, the city and state first confirmed case must be verified by provincial centers for Disease Control and prevention before it can be confirmed as a confirmed case. It takes about 2-3 days for the recheck results to return, which is why the information of confirmed cases was not released until three days after the suspected cases were announced.

From the second case, no longer need provincial CDC audit confirmation, the city can test and confirm the results.

"The number of confirmed cases is increasing rapidly, but it is impossible to tell whether this is due to the disposal of previously untested samples or the fact of new cases, " I read in an article in China Newsweek, john  Johan, a scientist at Johns Hopkins University in the US.

Tomorrow, how many people will be diagnosed?
